      "title": "Time as a Disqualifying Factor at Private Altars: Whether the Requirement to Avoid Sleeping Over (Notar) Applies at Private Altars",
      "display_title": "Time at Private Altars",
      "timestamp": "24:14",
      "micro_segments": [
        {
          "title": "The Question: How Do We Know Time (Sleeping Over) Creates Disqualification at Private Altars When Space Is Not an Issue?",
          "display_title": "Initial Question",
          "timestamp": "24:14"
        },
        {
          "title": "Logical Argument: Since Space Has No Restrictions at Private Altars, Neither Should Time Be Restricted",
          "display_title": "Space-Time Logic",
          "timestamp": "24:31"
        },
        {
          "title": "Counter-Argument Via Kal Va-Chomer from Birds: Blemishes Are Not an Issue for Birds, Yet Time Disqualifies Them, Suggesting Time Supersedes Space",
