          "timestamp": "25:46"
        },
        {
          "title": "Objection: Birds Are Different Because They Require a Kohen; Private Altars Don't, So the Parallel Fails",
          "display_title": "Objection to Comparison",
          "timestamp": "26:39"
        },
        {
          "title": "Resolution: The Word 'Torah' in 'This Is the Teaching of the Sheep-Offering' Is Inclusive, Including All Disqualifying Factors for Both Altar Types",
          "display_title": "Inclusive 'Torah'",
          "timestamp": "27:20"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "title": "Concluding Theological Reflection: The Preeminence of Time Over Space in Jewish Sanctity",
      "display_title": "Time Over Space",
      "timestamp": "27:42",
      "micro_segments": [
        {
          "title": "The Masechet Ends with a Principle: Even at Private Altars Where Space Restrictions Don't Apply, Time Restrictions Still Bind",
